{"id": 529, "text": "\"41Regulation 19 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 19 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 530, "text": "\"\\u201cCreation of security for secured debentures.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 531, "text": "\"19.(1) The debentures shall be secured by the creation of a charge, on the properties or assets or the receivables of the issuer, having a value which is sufficient for the due repayment of the amount of debentures and interest thereon:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 532, "text": "\"Provided that in case unsecured debentures are intended to be listed on stock exchange(s), then such debt securities shall either be backed by guarantee from State Government or Central Government or shall have a structured payment mechanism whereby the issuer shall deposit debt servicing amounts in the designated bank account at least 10 working days before due date of payment.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 533, "text": "\"(2)The total value of secured debentures issued shall not exceed the market value of immovable property/other assets or receivables of the issuer, for which a charge shall be created.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 534, "text": "\"(3)The issuer shall give an undertaking in the offer document that the assets on which charge is created are free from any encumbrances and if the assets are already charged to secure a debt, the permissions or consent to create second or pari pasu charge on the assets of the issuer have been obtained from the earlier creditor.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 535, "text": "\"(4)The issue proceeds shall not be utilised until the documents for creation of security are executed.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 536, "text": "\"Page - 24 - of 68\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 537, "text": "\"42[Trust deed.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 538, "text": "\"20. (1) A trust deed for securing the issue of municipal debt securities shall be executed by the issuer in favour of the debenture trustee.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 539, "text": "\"(2)The trust deed shall contain such clauses as may be specified in Schedule IV of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Debenture Trustees) Regulations, 1993:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 540, "text": "\"Provided that in case of private placement by a body corporate to which the Companies Act, 2013 applies, the trust deed shall, in-addition contain such clauses as required under section 71 of the Companies Act, 2013 and the Companies (Share Capital and Debentures) Rules 2014.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 541, "text": "\"(3)The trust deed shall not contain a clause which has the effect of:\\n(a)limiting or extinguishing the obligations and liabilities of the debenture trustees or the issuer in relation to any rights or interests of the investors;\\n(b)limiting or restricting or waiving the provisions of the Act, or Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 or the Depositories Act, 1996, and the regulations and circulars or guidelines issued by the Board from time to time;\\n(c)indemnifying the debenture trustees or the issuer for loss or damage caused by their act of negligence or commission or omission.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 542, "text": "\"(4)The issue proceeds shall not be utilised until the Trust deed is executed.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 543, "text": "\"42Regulation 20 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 20 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 544, "text": "\"20.(1) A trust deed for securing the issue of debentures shall be executed by the issuer in favour of the independent trustee or debenture trustee, as applicable, within three months of the closure of the issue.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 545, "text": "\"(2) The trust deed shall contain such clauses as may be prescribed in Schedule IV of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Debenture Trustees) Regulations, 1993:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 546, "text": "\"Provided that in case of private placement by a corporate municipal entity, the trust deed shall, in- addition, contain such clauses as prescribed under section 71 of the Companies Act, 2013 and Companies (Share Capital and Debentures) Rules 2014.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 547, "text": "\"(3) The trust deed shall not contain a clause which has the effect of:\\n(a)limiting or extinguishing the obligations and liabilities of the debenture trustees or the issuer in relation to any rights or interests of the investors;\\n(b)limiting or restricting or waiving the provisions of the Act, these regulations and circulars or guidelines issued by the Board;\\n(c)indemnifying the debenture trustees or the issuer for loss or damage caused by their act of negligence or commission or omission.\\u201d\\nPage - 25 - of 68\\n43[Redemption and roll-over.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 548, "text": "\"21. (1) The issuer shall redeem the municipal debt securities in terms of the offer document or placement memorandum.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 549, "text": "\"(2) Where the issuer desires to roll-over the municipal debt securities issued, it shall do so only upon passing of a special resolution to that effect and give twenty one days\\u2019 notice of the proposed roll over to the holders of municipal debt securities:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 550, "text": "\"Provided that, if the holders of municipal debt securities do not provide consent for the proposed roll over within the notice period, the issuer shall redeem the municipal debt securities of such holders.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 551, "text": "\"(3)The notice referred to in sub- regulation (2) shall contain disclosures with regard to credit rating and the rationale for roll-over.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 552, "text": "\"43Regulation 21 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 21 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 553, "text": "\"\\u201cRedemption and roll-over.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 554, "text": "\"21.(1) The issuer shall redeem the debt securities in terms of the offer document.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 560, "text": "\"(5)The debt securities issued can be rolled over subject to the following conditions:\\n(a)The roll-over is approved by a special resolution passed by the holders of debt securities through postal ballot having the consent of not less than 75% of the holders by value of such debt securities:\\nProvided that this condition shall not be applicable to the issuer, which is a municipality: Provided further that in case of issuer being a municipality, a period of seven days shall be granted to the holders of debt securities to provide their consent;\\n(b)atleast one rating is obtained from a credit rating agency within a period of six months prior to the due date of redemption and is disclosed in the notice referred to in sub-regulation (2);\\n(c)fresh trust deed shall be executed at the time of such roll over or the existing trust deed may be continued if the trust deed provides for such continuation ;\\n(d)adequate security shall be created or maintained in respect of such debt securities to be rolled\\u2013 over.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 561, "text": "\"(6)The issuer shall redeem the debt securities of all the holders, who have not given their positive consent to the roll-over.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 562, "text": "\"Page - 26 - of 68\\n(4)The issuer shall, prior to sending the notice to holders of municipal debt securities, file a copy of the notice and proposed resolution with the stock exchanges where such securities are listed, for dissemination of the same to the public on their websites.\\n(5)The municipal debt securities issued can be rolled over subject to the following conditions:\\n(a)the roll-over is approved by a special resolution passed by the holders of such municipal debt securities having the consent of not less than 75% of the holders by value of such municipal debt securities:\\n(b)at least one rating is obtained from a credit rating agency within a period of six months prior to the due date of redemption and is disclosed in the notice referred to in sub-regulation (2);\\n(c)fresh trust deed shall be executed at the time of such roll over or the existing trust deed may be continued if the trust deed provides for such continuation;\\n(6)The issuer shall redeem the municipal debt securities of all the holders, who have not given their positive consent to the roll-over.]\\n44[Face value of municipal debt securities\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 563, "text": "\"22.The face value of municipal debt securities shall be disclosed in offer document or placement memorandum in the manner as specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 564, "text": "\"Day count convention\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 565, "text": "\"22A. The day count convention for calculation of interest payments for municipal debt securities shall be Actual/Actual and shall be calculated in manner as specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 566, "text": "\"44Regulation 22 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 22 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 567, "text": "\"\\u201cDebenture redemption reserve.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 568, "text": "\"22.(1) For the redemption of the debentures issued by a corporate municipal entity, the issuer shall create debenture redemption reserve in accordance with the provisions of the Companies Act, 2013 and the rules made thereunder.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 569, "text": "\"(2) Where the issuer is a corporate municipal entity and the issuer has defaulted in payment of interest on debt securities or redemption thereof or in creation of security as per the terms of the issue of debt securities, any distribution of dividend shall require approval of the debenture trustees.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 570, "text": "\"Page - 27 - of 68\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 571, "text": "\"Prohibition on payment of incentives\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 572, "text": "\"22B. Any person connected with the issue shall not offer any incentive, whether direct or indirect, in any manner, whether in cash or kind or services or otherwise to any person for making an application in the issue, except for fees or commission for services rendered in relation to the issue.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 573, "text": "\"23. (1) The issuer making public issues of municipal debt securities or seeking listing of municipal debt securities issued on private placement basis, shall comply with the conditions of listing specified in Schedule V of these regulations including continuous disclosure and other requirements specified by the Board from time to time.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 574, "text": "\"45 Inserted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 575, "text": "\"46Regulation 23 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 23 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 576, "text": "\"\\u201cContinuous listing conditions.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 577, "text": "\"23.(1) All the issuers making public issues of debt securities or seeking listing of debt securities issued on private placement basis, shall comply with conditions of listing including continuous disclosure and other requirements specified by the Board in general and those specified in Schedule V to these regulations.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 578, "text": "\"(2) Where the issuer is corporate municipal entity, one-third of its Board shall comprise of independent directors, as defined in section 149 of the Companies Act, 2013.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 579, "text": "\"(3) Every rating obtained by an issuer shall be periodically reviewed by the registered credit rating agency and any revision in the rating shall be promptly disclosed by the issuer to the stock exchange(s) where the debt securities are listed.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 580, "text": "\"(4) In the event of credit rating being downgraded by two or more notches below the rating assigned at the time of issue, the issuer shall present to all bondholders, the reasons for fall in rating and the steps, if any, it intends to take to recover the rating.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 581, "text": "\"(5) Any change in rating shall be promptly disseminated in such manner as the stock exchange where such securities are listed may determine from time to time.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 582, "text": "\"(6) The issuer, the respective debenture trustees, wherever appointed, and stock exchanges shall disseminate all information and reports regarding debt securities including compliance reports filed by the issuers and the debenture trustees, if appointed, to the investors and the general public by placing them on their websites.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 583, "text": "\"(7) The information referred to in sub-regulation (5) shall also be placed on the websites, if any, of the debenture trustee, the issuer and the stock exchanges.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 584, "text": "\"Page - 28 - of 68\\n(2)Where the issuer is a body corporate to whom the Companies Act, 2013 applies, one-third of its Board shall comprise of independent directors, as defined in section 149 of the Companies Act, 2013.\\n(3)Any change in rating shall be promptly disseminated in such manner as the stock exchange where such securities are listed may determine from time to time.\\n(4)The issuer, the respective debenture trustees, and stock exchanges shall disseminate all information and reports regarding municipal debt securities including compliance reports filed by the issuers and the debenture trustees, to the investors and the general public by placing them on their websites.\\n(5)The information referred to in sub-regulation (3) shall also be placed on the websites of the debenture trustee, the issuer and the stock exchanges.]\\n47[Accounting and audit.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 585, "text": "\"24.(1) An issuer shall prepare accounts in any of the manner specified in clause (b) of regulation 4:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 586, "text": "\"Provided that in case the Issuer is a body corporate to which the Companies Act, 2013 applies, the accounts shall be prepared in accordance with section 129 and 134 of the Companies Act, 2013 and the rules made thereunder.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 587, "text": "\"(2) In case of the issuer being a municipality, the accounts of the issuer shall be audited by the persons appointed by the municipal corporations, as permissible under its constitution document:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 588, "text": "\"47Regulation 24 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 24 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 589, "text": "\"\\u201cAccounting and audit.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 590, "text": "\"24.(1) An Issuer, being a municipality, shall prepare its accounts in accordance with the National Municipal Accounts Manual or in accordance with similar Municipal Accounts Manual adopted by the respective State Government:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 591, "text": "\"Provided that in case of the Issuer being a corporate municipal entity, the accounts shall be prepared in accordance with section 129 and 134 of the Companies Act, 2013 and the rules made thereunder.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 592, "text": "\"(2) In case of the issuer being a municipality, the accounts of the issuer shall be audited by the persons appointed by the municipal corporations, as permissible under its constitution/state legislation governing the municipality:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 593, "text": "\"Provided that in case of an issuer being a corporate municipal entity, the accounts of the issuer shall be audited by an auditor, in terms of section 139 of the Companies Act, 2013 and the rules made thereunder:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 594, "text": "\"(3) The bank account for issue proceeds and separate escrow account with earmarked revenues, shall be audited by persons so appointed by the municipality or the corporate municipal entity, within six months of the close of every financial year.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 595, "text": "\"Page - 29 - of 68\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 596, "text": "\"Provided that in case the issuer is a body corporate to which the Companies Act, 2013 applies, the accounts of the issuer shall be audited by an auditor, in terms of section 139 of the Companies Act, 2013 and the Rules made thereunder.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 597, "text": "\"48[Trading and reporting of municipal debt securities.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 598, "text": "\"25.(1) The trades of listed municipal debt securities shall be cleared and settled through a recognised clearing corporation in the manner specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 599, "text": "\"(2)In case of trades in municipal debt securities which have been made over the counter, such trades shall be reported on a recognised stock exchange having a nationwide trading terminal or such other platform as may be specified by the Board from time to time.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 600, "text": "\"(3) The information in respect of issues such as issuer details, instrument details, ratings, rating migration, coupon, buyback etc. shall be required to be reported to a common database as may be specified by the Board.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 601, "text": "\"48Regulation 25 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 25 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 602, "text": "\"\\u201cTrading and reporting of debt securities.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 603, "text": "\"25.(1) The debt securities issued to the public or on a private placement basis, which are listed in recognised stock exchanges, shall be traded and such trades shall be cleared and settled in recognised clearing corporation subject to conditions specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 604, "text": "\"(2) The trading lot for privately placed debt securities shall be rupees one lakh or such amount as may be specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 605, "text": "\"(3) In case of trades of debt securities which have been made over the counter, such trades shall be reported on a recognised stock exchange having a nationwide trading terminal or such other platform as may be specified by the Board from time to time.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 606, "text": "\"(4) The information in respect of issues such as issuer details, instrument details, ratings, rating migration, coupon, buyback, redemption details, shall be required to be reported to a common database with depositories or any other platform as may be specified by the Board.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 607, "text": "\"Page - 30 - of 68\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 608, "text": "\"26. (1) The debenture trustee shall be vested with the requisite powers for protecting the interest of holders of municipal debt securities:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 609, "text": "\"Provided that, where the issuer is a body corporate to which the Companies Act, 2013 applies such powers shall include a right to appoint a nominee director on the Board of the issuer, in consultation with institutional holders of such securities.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 610, "text": "\"(2)The debenture trustee shall carry out its duties and perform its functions in terms of these regulations, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Debenture Trustees) Regulations, 1993, the trust deed and the offer document/placement memorandum, with due care, diligence and loyalty.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 611, "text": "\"(3)The debenture trustee shall monitor the separate escrow account maintained in respect of the earmarked revenue.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 612, "text": "\"(4)The debenture trustee shall ensure disclosure of all material events on an ongoing basis.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 613, "text": "\"49Regulation 26 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 26 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 616, "text": "\"(2) The monitoring agency shall inspect on half yearly basis, the utilization of issue proceeds in accordance with objects of the issue as specified in offer document and report, material deviation, if any, to the concerned stock exchange for public dissemination.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 617, "text": "\"(3) The monitoring agency shall monitor earmarked revenue in the separate escrow account.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 618, "text": "\"(4) The debenture trustee, wherever appointed, shall be vested with the requisite powers for protecting the interest of holders of debt securities:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 619, "text": "\"Provided that , where the issuer is a corporate municipal entity, such powers shall include a right to appoint a nominee director on the Board of the issuer, in consultation with institutional holders of such securities.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 620, "text": "\"(5) the debenture trustee, wherever appointed, shall disclose the information to the investors and the general public by issuing a press release in any of the following events:\\n(a)default by issuer to pay interest on debt securities or redemption amount;\\n(b)failure to create a charge on the assets;\\n(c)revision of rating assigned to the debt securities.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 621, "text": "\"(6)The debenture trustee, wherever appointed, shall carry out its duties and perform its functions under these regulations, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Debenture Trustees) Regulations, 1993, the trust deed and offer document, with due care, diligence and loyalty.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 622, "text": "\"(7)The debenture trustee, wherever appointed, shall ensure disclosure of all material events on an ongoing basis\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 623, "text": "\"(8)The debenture trustees, wherever appointed, shall supervise the implementation of the conditions regarding creation of security for the debt securities and debenture redemption reserve.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 624, "text": "\"Page - 31 - of 68\\n(5)The debenture trustee shall supervise the implementation of the obligations cast in terms of provisions of these regulations.]\\n50[Obligations of the issuer and merchant banker.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 625, "text": "\"27. (1) The issuer shall disclose all the material facts in the offer documents issued or distributed to the public and shall ensure that all the disclosures made in the offer document are true, fair and adequate and there is no mis-leading or untrue statements or mis-statement in the offer document.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 626, "text": "\"(2)The merchant banker(s) shall verify and confirm that the disclosures made in the offer documents are true, fair and adequate and ensure that the issuer is in compliance with these regulations.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 627, "text": "\"(3)The merchant banker(s) shall ensure that all transaction specific disclosures required in Schedule I of these regulations are complied with:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 628, "text": "\"Provided that where the issuer is a body corporate to which the Companies Act, 2013 applies, the merchant banker(s) shall also ensure that the disclosures under Companies Act, 2013 and rules made thereunder are complied with.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 629, "text": "\"(4)The issuer shall treat the applicants in a public issue of municipal debt securities in a fair and equitable manner as per the procedures as may be specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 630, "text": "\"(5)The merchant bankers shall be responsible for the due diligence in respect of assignments undertaken by them in respect of issue, offer and distribution of securities to the public.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 631, "text": "\"50Regulation 27 substituted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its substitution, regulation 27 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 632, "text": "\"\\u201cObligations of the issuer and merchant banker.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 633, "text": "\"27.(1) The issuer shall disclose all the material facts in the offer documents issued or distributed to the public and shall ensure that all the disclosures made in the offer document are true, fair and adequate and there is no mis-leading or untrue statements or mis-statement in the offer document.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 634, "text": "\"(2) The merchant banker(s) shall verify and confirm that the disclosures made in the offer documents are true, fair and adequate and ensure that the issuer is in compliance with these regulations.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 635, "text": "\"(3) The merchant banker(s) shall ensure that all transaction specific disclosures required in Schedule I of these regulations are complied with:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 636, "text": "\"Provided where the issuer is a corporate municipal entity, merchant banker(s) shall also ensure that the disclosures under Companies Act, 2013 and rules made thereunder are complied with.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 637, "text": "\"(4) The issuer shall treat the applicants in a public issue of debt securities in a fair and equitable manner as per the procedures as may be specified by the Board.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 638, "text": "\"(5) The issuer and merchant bankers shall be responsible for the due diligence in respect of assignments undertaken by them in respect of issue, offer and distribution of securities to the public.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 639, "text": "\"(6) No person shall employ any device, scheme or artifice to defraud in connection with issue or subscription or distribution of debt securities which are listed or proposed to be listed on a recognised stock exchange.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 640, "text": "\"(7) The issuer and the merchant bankers shall ensure that the security created to secure the debt securities is adequate to ensure hundred per cent. asset cover for the debt securities.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 641, "text": "\"Page - 32 - of 68\\n(6)There shall be no conflict of interest between the lead manager(s) and the issuer or its group companies in accordance with the applicable regulations.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 642, "text": "\"27A. Without prejudice to the action under section 11, 11A, 11 B, 11D, sub- section (3) of section 12, Chapter VIA and section 24 of the Act or section 439 of the Companies Act, 2013, the Board may suo-motu or upon receipt of information or on completion or pendency of inspection or investigation, in the interests of the securities market, issue or pass such directions as it deems fit including any or all of the following:\\n(a)direct the issuer to refund the application monies to the applicants in a public issue;\\n(b)direct the persons concerned not to further deal in securities in any particular manner;\\n(c)direct the persons concerned not to access the securities market for a specified period;\\n(d)restrain the issuer or its promoters or directors from making further issues of securities;\\n(e)direct the person concerned to sell or divest the securities;\\n(f)direct the issuer or the depository not to give effect transfer or directing further freeze of transfer of securities;\\n(g)any other direction which Board may deem fit and proper in the circumstances of the case:\\nProvided that the Board shall, either before or after issuing such directions, give an opportunity of being heard to the persons against whom the directions are issued or proposed to be issued:\\nProvided further that if any ex-parte direction is required to be urgent issued, the Board may give post decisional hearing to the affected person:\\n51 Inserted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019.\\nPage - 33 - of 68\\nProvided also that where the issuer is a Municipality, the Board may communicate the instances of violation or non-compliance etc. if any, to the Central Government and the concerned State Government.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 643, "text": "\"27B. (1) The Board may, exempt any person or class of persons from the operation of all or any of the provisions of these regulations for a period as may be specified but not exceeding twelve months, for furthering innovation in technological aspects relating to testing new products, processes, services, business models, etc. in live environment of regulatory sandbox in the securities markets.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 644, "text": "\"(2)Any exemption granted by the Board under sub-regulation (1) shall be subject to the applicant satisfying such conditions as may be specified by the Board including conditions to be complied with on a continuous basis.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 645, "text": "\"Explanation. \\u2014 For the purposes of these regulations, \\\"regulatory sandbox\\\" means a live testing environment where new products, processes, services, business models, etc. may be deployed on a limited set of eligible customers for a specified period of time, for furthering innovation in the securities market, subject to such conditions as may be specified by the Board.]\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 646, "text": "\"29.In order to remove any difficulties in the interpretation or application of the provisions of these regulations, the Board shall have the power to issue directions through guidance notes or circulars:\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 647, "text": "\"52Inserted by the SEBI (Regulatory Sandbox) (Amendment) Regulations, 2020, w.e.f. 17-04-2020.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 648, "text": "\"53Omitted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019. Prior to its omission, regulation 28 read as follows,-\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 649, "text": "\"\\u201cSanction for violations.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 650, "text": "\"28.Any contravention of these regulations shall be dealt with by the Board in accordance with the Act.\\u201d\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 651, "text": "\"Page - 34 - of 68\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 652, "text": "\"Provided that where any direction is issued by the Board in a specific case relating to interpretation or application of any provision of these regulations, it shall be done only after affording a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the concerned persons and after recording reasons for the direction.\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 653, "text": "\"54[Power to relax strict enforcement of Regulations\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
{"id": 654, "text": "\"30. The Board may, in the interest of investors or for the development of the securities market, relax the strict enforcement of any requirement of these regulations, if the Board is satisfied that, -\\n(a)the requirement is procedural or technical in nature; or\\n(b)the requirement may cause undue hardship to investors; or\\n(c)the disclosure requirement is not relevant for a particular industry or class of issuers;\\nor\\n(d)the non-compliance was caused due to factors beyond the control of the issuer ;or\\n(e)such relaxation will be in the interest of securities market.]\\n54 Inserted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Issue and Listing of Debt Securities by Municipalities) (Amendment) Regulations, 2019 w.e.f. 27.09.2019.\\nPage - 35 - of 68\\n\"", "meta": {}, "annotation_approver": null, "labels": []}
